<br>
For me, love is defined when I look at the person I'm laying next to while they are still sleeping and I try to imagine my life without her. It's joy that she's here with me. It's pain, the heart wrenching, gut twisting knowledge that one day I'll have to live without her.  It's excitement at all the wonderful experiances we've had together, and look foreward to having. It's fear as I have never felt any other way of the day she leaves me. <br>
<br>
Love comes in many forms.<br>
<br>
Sometimes love is like when I was young, insistant, consuming, demanding. Sometimes it's gentle, touching and patient. More and more these days I realize that the fire I always thought love to be is only the beginning. Many people loose love once that fire is gone, I myself have passed that phase and have settled into the slow calming warmth that is the strength my partner lends me throughout my day. I cherish that more than any moment of direct passion from our past. It gives me the strength to keep going. <br>
<br>
That's how I feel on the romanitical true love emotion you expressed intrest in. However there is more than that. <br>
<br>
Friendship is a love in and of itself. Family is too.<br>
<br>
As much as my partner nourishes and sooths my soul now my friends have helped shape who I am, what I have become. I love them for that. Recently I left my hometown, I took for granted the day to day presence of people who accepted and understood me, and who supported me unconditionally. They will never know how deeply they have affected my life, nor can I ever ever thank them enough. You are at a phase where friends come and go, they did for me, and they do for everyone to varying degrees. Treasure your time with them. Let them know how much you feel for them, if you don't now you may never have the chance to do so.<br>
<br>
As for family, this you cannot pick. But they too shaped who you are and what you will become. Thank them, they deserve that much. And if they treat you well, love them, let them know that.  If they don't treat you well, do not dwell on it, your health and happieness is more important than bonds of blood.<br>
<br>
Love is a four letter word for every emotion you could ever hope to encounter because it will eventually lead you to experiance all of them. Hate, Loathing and Malice can all be the product of love. If you doubt me, wait until someone hurts the one you hold dear. <br>
<br>
I'm just a sappy romantic at heart, I can't help it. I'm sorry. <br>
<br>
And before you worry over much about love, be happy. Be healthy. Live long and prosper. And just rember what Sting said in &quot; Love is Stronger than Justice &quot; ...  Love is a big fat river in Flood .<br>
<br>
Grab a paddle boy you're gonna need it. <br>
<br>
~ PoLith ~ who may or may not be insane =P<br>
