<br>
I don't think that love is some overarching thing that controls people, some weird force or something.  You don't just fall in love and live happily ever after.  Relationships take work.  Love is like planting a garden.  You have to plant the seeds and water them every day, or they'll wither and die.  You can't take it for granted.  I've seen what that's like - my parents take a very casual attitude towards their relationship, and barely treat each other with respect anymore.  It's really sad.  You have to be willing to work for your relationship, and to compromise.<br>
<br>
Some people may think that what I'm talking about isn't love, and is some &quot;lesser&quot; emotion, but really.  Not everything comes naturally, even when you're in love.  Your partner won't know exactly what you need without being told, and neither will you know everything your partner needs.  You need to trust each other, respect each other, and try to make it work.<br>
<br>
