A wise man once said, &quot;Choose your love, Love your choice.&quot;  I try to apply that on a daily basis with my wife.  To truly gain the more abstract noun form of love, we need to love the person we feel attracted to.  This means showing love to her through service to her, kind deeds, compliments, thoughtful gifts, speaking with her/listening to her(women want this more than most things you can give), and thinking about her well being on a regular basis.  <br>
A relationship was never meant to be 50/50.  We are not to give 50% of ourselves and then expect them to give 50% of themselves.  That almost always leaves us feeling that we have done our part and the other owes us something.  We are to give 100% or more, to make our best effort, and expect nothing in return.  THAT is loving someone, and such love is rarely non-reciprocated by one worthy of such love resulting in a strong 100/100 relationship.<br>
Unfortunately, today's society focuses more and more on pleasing ourselves and asking the question, &quot;What do I get out of it?&quot;  If one enters a relationship doing so to simply satisfy his own lust or because she makes him feel good, the relationship will last only as long as she continues to satisfy that lust or continues to make him feel good unless he takes action and begins to get beyond HIS needs and places HER needs in higher priority.  Of course, such action can lead to marriage if she decides to begin thinking about his needs more than her own.<br>
The point of all of this is, a woman can fulfill the needs of a man better than the man can himself.  (sex is a great example of this, but is goes much further than that)  Likewise, a man can fulfill the needs of a woman better than she can alone.  When we realize this and fill those needs of the one we love, and the one we love fills our needs, the relationship is strong and lasting.  Both parties have their needs, and likely their wants, met and both are very happy. <br>
