<br>
Love is something this jaded romantic has tried time and again to define, and failed.  Love has meant many different things to me in my life.<br>
<br>
Love is all-consuming passion.<br>
<br>
Love is tenderness and roses on Valentine's Day.<br>
<br>
Love is respect.<br>
<br>
Love is a deeply felt connection, as if you've always known that person from before time began.<br>
<br>
Love is a ripping, tearing, rending pain that you are sure will kill you.<br>
<br>
Love is spanning distances of thousands of miles with a single thought.<br>
<br>
Love is a hug when you're sure no one cares anymore.<br>
<br>
Love is no regrets, and every regret you've ever had.<br>
<br>
Love is knowing your life is more complete because you had them in it.<br>
<br>
Love is visiting a grave and knowing that person is still with you, even in death.<br>
<br>
Love is the double-edged sword you hold, even though you could cut yourself with it.<br>
<br>
Love is everything, and anything.<br>
<br>
Love is endless possibilities.<br>
<br>
Love is my future, and my past.<br>
