<br>
I didn't think I could still cry about this.<br>
<br>
....<br>
<br>
Much of my life I have been an incredible skeptic and cynic.<br>
<br>
I used to not believe in love, or at least that other people had feelings and ascribed the word &quot;love&quot; to whatever it was that they felt.<br>
<br>
Then I fell in love.  It went from fascination and &quot;I think I could live a long time with you,&quot; to lovers and partners, to absolute best friend.  Someone I didn't have to hide any thought from.  A mutual &quot;I don't know how I could ever live without you.&quot;  Someone who became for me an integral part of who I am.<br>
<br>
We spent much of what I consider my adult life together.<br>
<br>
I knew absolutely in whose arms I planned to take my last breath.<br>
<br>
Now that person is gone...<br>
<br>
...the third time in my life I have lost a best friend to circumstances I couldn't control. <br>
<br>
The first was my sister, my childhood friend above all others, we began to grow apart at puberty but illness deteriorated and demolished her in slow motion into something totally unrecognizable as the friend I once knew.<br>
<br>
The second was my dog, laugh if you want - but I really didn't  have friends as a teenager - I watched her being born, and when in old age she succumbed to illness, I was the one that put her to death.<br>
<br>
The third ...<br>
<br>
...ended in a way that destroyed what I had come to believe love was, destroyed my view of people, destroyed my view of life...<br>
<br>
...probably, I'm still in shock.<br>
<br>
I spent most of last year believing essentially that I wear a coat of thorns.  That when I really reach out to touch someone elses heart, they and I both get hurt.<br>
<br>
The panic attacks at night, the bizarre sensation that I'm being physically struck by ghosts, crying every day feeling the stabbing feeling in my heart and abdomen, constriction of the throat, wanting to exhale till I can't anymore and then stop breathing - only to be betrayed by my body over and over again...<br>
<br>
...they have all passed into another reality now.<br>
<br>
All friendships I severed, because no longer believe they were friends.  I trust no one, including myself.  Reality it seems, is a figment of my imagination.<br>
<br>
Three years after knowing it was ending I am still learning to be really, truly, alone.<br>
<br>
Looking back with hindsight it seems to me that we form a construct in our mind of the other person - and fall in love with the construct - not the entirety of who the other person really is.  <br>
<br>
I know for certain that being together in love there were problems, life never works out perfectly or goes how you expect it to... at least it has not for me.  But I know it was the happiest time in my life.  I am still in love with the construct in my mind even though I know that the entirety of the person and the construct are not one and the same, maybe they never were, and I can never see things the same way again.<br>
 <br>
Ninichka<br>
